      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey my car keeps stalling when i'm idling at lights and sometimes the lights flicker too. i think it might be the alternator? can u explain whats that actually do and what the signs are that it's dying?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The alternator is the car's battery charger, and it's the only thing that keeps the battery from draining while you're driving. If it's failing, your car will eventually run out of power and die, but first, you'll notice the lights flickering and the engine stalling when you're idling at a light. That's because the alternator isn't producing enough electricity to keep the battery charged, so the car's electrical system runs on a depleted battery.\n\nThe signs of a dying alternator are often subtle but tell-tale. You'll see the dashboard lights flicker or dim when you turn the engine off, and the battery warning light on your dashboard will start blinking. If you've ever had to jump-start your car after a long trip, that's a classic sign of a failing alternator. Additionally, if the battery is old or weak, it might not hold a charge even when the alternator is working, which can cause the same symptoms.\n\nTo fix the issue, you'll need to check the alternator's output with a multimeter or have a mechanic test it. If the alternator is indeed failing, you may need to replace it, which can be a bit of a hassle since it",
